            <fr:title text="Can we treat \mathsf {\mathbf {*}} as \mathsf {\mathbf {B}}?">Can we treat <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {*}}]]></fr:tex> as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {B}}]]></fr:tex>?</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Again, suppose we have a strong Kleene valuation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v]]></fr:tex>.
Let's try a different tack this time, to see if we can treat the value <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {*}}]]></fr:tex> like <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {B}}]]></fr:tex> instead.
That is, let's set up a Dunn-Belnap valuation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> so that, for every atomic sentence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we have:
<html:ul><html:li>if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v(A) = \mathsf {\mathbf {T}}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {F}}]]></fr:tex> then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t(A) = v(A)]]></fr:tex>, and</html:li>
<html:li>if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v(A) = \mathsf {\mathbf {*}}]]></fr:tex> then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t(A) = \mathsf {\mathbf {B}}.]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul></html:p>
            <html:p>This certainly determines <html:em>some</html:em> Dunn-Belnap valuation; but as before, we can't say much about the result yet.
It would be convenient if the above property turns out to hold for <html:em>all</html:em> sentences, not just the atomic ones.
As before, we can attempt to show this via induction.
For convenience, let's call this property "the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {*}} / \mathsf {\mathbf {B}}]]></fr:tex> property"; note that it's a different property from the one we looked at before.
(Note, though, that there's nothing particularly important about this property in its own right; we're just using it for a moment, to reason by induction.)
I'll go through the reasoning a bit quicker this time, so you can see the pattern again.</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/lectures/ellieripley/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://negation.rocks/lectures/ellieripley/" display-uri="ellieripley" type="local">Ellie Ripley</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>28</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
